      "order": 1,
      "Description": "Autonomous transport systems are designed to operate independently, but there are critical moments when a human operator must step in to ensure safety and maintain control. This lesson introduces the key principles behind human override, exploring the circumstances that require intervention and the correct procedures for taking manual control of an autonomous vehicle or system. You will learn to recognise warning signs, system alerts, and environmental conditions that signal the need for operator action. The content is presented in a practical, straightforward way, making it accessible to those who are new to working with autonomous transport technology. By the end of this lesson, you will have a clear understanding of your responsibilities as an operator and the confidence to act decisively when a situation demands it.",
